<subSubSection id="689C65087F17FFE5FF6E5BF0FD90FC16" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" type="description">
<paragraph id="203936837F17FFE5FF6E5BF0FDEDFD1A" blockId="17.[151,1436,618,967]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FF6E5BF0FBA7FD76" bold="true" box="[199,1049,654,679]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">Recorded damage and economic importance in the orchards of Iran:</emphasis>
A pest in vineyards (
<bibRefCitation id="44174B727F17FFE5FAB05BF1FEDEFD1A" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" refId="ref20473" refString="Mostaan, M. &amp; Akbarzadeh, G. (1995) Studies on the egg parasitoid of the grape vine leafhopper (Arboridia kermanshah). Trichogramma and other egg parasitoids. 4 th International Symposium, Cairo, Egypt, 1995, 201 - 202." type="journal article">Mostaan &amp; Akbarzadeh 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="44174B727F17FFE5FEC55BCCFDF6FD1A" box="[364,584,690,715]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" refId="ref19980" refString="Latifian, M., Seyedoleslami, H. &amp; Khajehali, J. (2004) Immature stages morphology, biology and seasonal population fluctuation of Arboridia kermanshah Dlabola (Hom.: Cicadellidae) in Isfahan province. Science and Technology of Agriculture and Natural Resources, 9, 205 - 216. [in Persian with English abstract]" type="journal article">
Latifian 
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FE655BCAFE43FD1A" box="[460,509,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="203936837F17FFE5FF6E5BA8FC44FCC2" blockId="17.[151,1436,618,967]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FF6E5BA8FC21FD3E" bold="true" box="[199,927,726,751]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">Recorded damage in the orchards of other parts of the world:</emphasis>
The species of this genus have been recorded as well known pests on vineyards in the world (
<bibRefCitation id="44174B727F17FFE5FD025B84FC81FCC2" box="[683,831,762,787]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" refId="ref21433" refString="Pombo, D. A. (2001) Arboridia erecta (Ribaut, 1931) (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae), a new leafhopper to the fauna of the Iberian Peninsula, and data on the distribution of Arboridia parvula (Boheman, 1845). Zoologica baetica, 12, 101 - 107." type="journal article">Pombo 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="44174B727F17FFE5FCE35B84FC51FCC2" box="[842,1007,762,787]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" refId="ref22384" refString="Viggiani, G. (2002) Egg parasitoids of vineyard leafhoppers and their alternative hosts in the Mediterranean Basin. Bollettino del Laboratorio di Entomologia Agria &quot; Filippo Silvestri &quot;, 58, 63 - 76." type="journal article">Viggiani 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="203936837F17FFE5FF6E5A60FB03FCE6" blockId="17.[151,1436,618,967]" box="[199,1213,798,823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FF6E5A60FD8CFCE6" bold="true" box="[199,562,798,823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">Recorded distribution in Iran:</emphasis>
West, centre and northeast (
<bibRefCitation id="44174B727F17FFE5FCC75A60FB0CFCE6" box="[878,1202,798,823]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" refId="ref20841" refString="Mozaffarian, F. &amp; Wilson, M. R. (2016) A checklist of the leafhoppers of Iran (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Zootaxa, 4062 (1), 1 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4062.1.1" type="journal article">Mozaffarian &amp; Wilson 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="203936837F17FFE5FF6E5A3CFD90FC16" blockId="17.[151,1436,618,967]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FF6E5A3CFEE8FC8A" bold="true" box="[199,342,834,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">Conclusion:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E7864D007F17FFE5FEC95A3DFDB2FC8A" baseAuthorityName="Dlabola" baseAuthorityYear="1963" box="[352,524,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Arboridia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kermanshah">
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FEC95A3DFDB2FC8A" box="[352,524,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">A. kermanshah</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an endemic species with a rather wide recorded distribution in Iran. It was recorded as a common species and a pest in Iranian vineyards of the country. The economic injury level for the species was determined by 
<bibRefCitation id="44174B727F17FFE5FE655AF4FD07FC72" box="[460,697,906,931]" pageId="17" pageNumber="492" refId="ref20042" refString="Latifian, M., Seyedoleslami, H. &amp; Khajehali, J. (2005) A model for tolerance threshold of the grape leafhopper Arboridia kermanshah Dlabola (Hom.: Cicadellidae). Journal of Science and Technology of Agriculture and Natural Resources, 9 (3), 231 - 240." type="journal article">
Latifian 
<emphasis id="12F2EA917F17FFE5FD855AF2FDE2FC72" box="[556,604,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="492">et al</emphasis>
. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, there isn’t any record available to indicate the damage level of the species in the vineyards.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
